  "prompt": "Is 291 a good score in gre?",
  "response": "A GRE score of 291 is typically considered below average. The GRE (Graduate Record Examination) is scored on a scale of 260 to 340, with the average score generally falling around 300. However, what constitutes a \"good\" score can vary significantly depending on the programs and schools to which you are applying. \n\nIf you're aiming for competitive graduate programs, especially in fields like engineering, business, or the sciences, you may want to aim for a score of 300 or higher. For humanities or some social sciences programs, the score requirements might be somewhat lower, but many master's programs still look for scores in the range of 300-320.\n\nIt's also important to consider the other components of your application, such as your undergraduate GPA, letters of recommendation, statement of purpose, and relevant experience. If you have a particularly strong profile in those areas, a lower GRE score might be balanced out.\n\nIf you're concerned about your score, you might consider studying for a retake of the exam if time allows before your application deadlines.",
